title: Intra - Africa free trade agreement
description:
A ratification instrument has been deposited by the South Africa government in Cairo, Egypt.
This will enhance free trade among three trading blocks on the African Continent.
The agreement will see the East African Community, the Common Market For Eastern and Southern Africa as well as SADC, trading freely.
Naledi Matlapeng reports from Cairo, Egypt.

For more news, visit: sabcnews.com
